        <updateDate>2019-07-31T13:44:36Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><strong>Research and Development Tax Credit Expansion Act of 2019</strong></p> <p>This bill&nbsp;modifies the refundable research tax credit for new and small businesses to (1) increase the limit on refundability to $500,000, with an adjustment for inflation; (2) allow refundable amounts to cover all payroll taxes paid by such businesses; and (3) extend eligibility for the credit to small businesses with less than $10 million in gross receipts (currently, less than $5 million).</p> <p>The bill also increases the rate of the alternative simplified tax credit for such businesses.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
